info.senderName: NWS Cheyenne (Southeastern Wyoming and Western Nebraska)
info.headline: High Wind Warning issued January 09 at 1:38PM MST until January 10 at 5:00PM MST by NWS Cheyenne
info.description: ...HIGH WIND WARNING IN EFFECT FROM 5 AM TO 5 PM MST TUESDAY... * WHAT...West winds 30 to 40 MPH with occasional gusts up to 60 MPH. * WHERE...Converse County Lower Elevations including Douglas and Deer Creek. The strongest winds will be along the foothills of the northern Laramie Range. * WHEN...5 AM MST until 5 PM MST Tuesday. * IMPACTS...Mainly to transportation. Strong cross winds will be hazardous to light weight and high profile vehicles, including campers and tractor trailers. Winds of this magnitude can also lead to property damage.
info.instruction: A High Wind Warning means a hazardous high wind event is expected or occurring. Sustained wind speeds of at least 40 mph or gusts of 58 mph or more can lead to property damage.
